I"<p>Test any changes to your <code>configuration.yaml</code> file before launching Home Assistant. This script allows you to test changes without the need to restart Home Assistant.</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash">$ hass --script check_config
</code></pre>
<p>The script has further options like checking configuration files which are not located in the default directory or showing your secrets for debugging.</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash">$ hass --script check_config -h
usage: hass [-h] [--script {check_config}] [-c CONFIG] [-i [INFO]] [-f] [-s]

Check Home Assistant configuration.

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --script {check_config}
  -c CONFIG, --config CONFIG
                        Directory that contains the Home Assistant
                        configuration
  -i [INFO], --info [INFO]
                        Show a portion of the config
  -f, --files           Show used configuration files
  -s, --secrets         Show secret information
</code></pre>
